The paper deals with deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that involves training agents to make decisions based on rewards. The paper also discusses the use of images as inputs, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The application of the method to robotics (cs.RO) is also mentioned. The paper proposes a new method for semi-supervised reinforcement learning, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
